we would all also agree there's a role from time to time for government to do a few
things. Joe talked movingly, and I totally agree with him, about immigration being such
a strength in America. You guys have a few problems to sort out with that, and you're
going to need government to act, and I don't see government acting. Now, you may
say, "It was ever thus. Washington has always been a mess." I'm a politician. I know
what people say about politicians. But Sarah Binder of Brookings did a study last year,
and she found that the likelihood of Congressional gridlock on a given issue has doubled
over the past 65 years. Your government is ineffective at a time when you need
effective government for yourselves and for the world.[TS]00:28:25[TE]Finally, and this to me is the biggest problem, this is the thing that really keeps me up at
